  "prompt": "Do people see questions that are marked as needing improvement?",
  "response": "If a question is marked as needing improvement on a specific platform, it typically means that its visibility might be reduced or it might be flagged for further editing before it is prominently displayed. The exact process can vary depending on the platform's policies and mechanisms.\n\n- On forums like Stack Overflow, questions that are marked as needing improvement might be downvoted or flagged by the community, which can result in reduced visibility. They may also be queued for review or editing.\n- In educational settings, such questions might be flagged by teachers or peers for revision.\n- On social media or Q&A sites, such posts could be less visible or temporarily hidden until edited.\n\nIf you are referring to a specific platform, their guidelines and help sections would provide the most accurate details regarding the visibility of questions marked as needing improvement.",
